post_text: Today we honor graduation senior Riley D'Angelo! Here is a message from her Homeroom Coach, Mr. Bob Worn: "I have always known you to persevere. You have shown it does not matter how slowly you go or what obstacles appear along the way, as long as you don’t stop. Keep going, find what you truly love to do and go for it. You have the ability. You just need to believe it in yourself. Graduating high school is proof enough.” Congratulations, Riley, on all you have accomplished!

Best Practices For Learning From Home: Help your child make a to-do list every day. Checking items off a list allows them to stay on task and gives them the satisfaction of knowing they completed all their work.
· Make the list in order of priority
· Write the list on a piece of paper rather than laptop
· Set time aside at the end of everyday to create tomorrow’s list

Attending school from home is routine for AHCCS students, but how have other PA students been adjusting to this new normal? Let us help you find success by tuning in everyday for a new tip or clicking the link below to see our full list!

AHCCS Senior Azaria "Ace" Garcia is directing a community musical as his graduation project. Directed by Ace and produced under the mentorship of Weary Arts Group, "Totally Gone With the Wind" is coming to York PA February 1st and 2nd! We ask that students, teachers and families in the area please consider attending and supporting him. Friday night is Dinner and a Show (fried chicken) and Saturday is show only. Click the link below for more information or contact Shannon Garcia!
https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=2669944033017508&id=100000058133353
